.TH "loop_set_size" 9 "loop_set_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
loop_set_size \- sets device size and notifies userspace
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" loop_set_size
.BI "(struct loop_device *lo "  ","
.BI "loff_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lo" 12
struct loop_device to set the size for
.IP "size" 12
new size of the loop device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Callers must validate that the size passed into this function fits into
a sector_t, eg using \fBloop_validate_size\fP
